\cf1\fs36 Introduction:\cf2\fs32\par
\cf3\fs28 The technology industry has experienced rapid growth in recent years, leading to a significant increase in the demand for programming and software development roles. As a result, understanding salary trends in different programming jobs has become important for students, job seekers, and professionals in the technology field.\par
This project focuses on analyzing salary data related to various programming and software development positions across different companies. The main goal of the project is to explore salary variations based on job titles and provide users with an easy way to search and view salary information for specific programming roles.\par
The system allows users to enter a job title, such as Frontend Developer, Backend Developer, or Software Engineer, and retrieve salary information from the dataset. The results display relevant companies and their corresponding salaries, helping users gain insights into salary distributions within the programming field.\par
In addition, the project includes a simple user interface designed to make the interaction with the dataset easier and more intuitive. The interface allows users to perform quick searches and view the results in a clear and organized format.\par
Overall, this project demonstrates how data analysis techniques can be applied to real-world datasets to extract meaningful insights and support better understanding of salary trends in the programming industry.\par
\fs22\par
\cf1\fs36 Dataset Description\cf3\fs22\par
\cf4\fs28 Web-Developers-Salaries-Egypt-2024\par
{\cf3\fs24{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/ibrahimzaitoun/web-developers-salaries-egypt-2024?utm_source=chatgpt.com }}{\fldrslt{https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/ibrahimzaitoun/web-developers-salaries-egypt-2024?utm_source=chatgpt.com\ul0\cf0}}}}\cf3\f0\fs24\par
\cf4 This dataset contains salary survey data for web developers (Back-end- Front-end - Full-Stack) in Egypt for the year 2024. The dataset encompasses various aspects of the profession, including:\par
\cf2 Title\cf4 : Job title or position of the developer .\par
\cf2 Salary\cf3\par
\cf2 Years of Experiences\cf3\par
\cf2 Work Hour \cf4 ( Part-time / Full-Time)\par
\cf2 Work Type \cf4 (Onsite / remotely / Hybrid )\par
Company Nationality\par
\cf2 Company site\cf3\par
\cf4 This dataset was compiled through a comprehensive survey targeting All Developers in Egypt.\par
\cf3\par
\fs28 Wuzzuf Job Listings Dataset (Egypt) - January 2025\fs24\par
{\fs22{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/ahmedhazemelabady/wuzzuf-job-listings-dataset-egypt-january-2025?utm_source=chatgpt.com }}{\fldrslt{https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/ahmedhazemelabady/wuzzuf-job-listings-dataset-egypt-january-2025?utm_source=chatgpt.com\ul0\cf0}}}}\f0\fs22\par
\cf1\fs28 Wuzzuf Job Listings Dataset\cf0\fs22\par
\cf4\fs24 This dataset contains 8,000+ job listings extracted from Wuzzuf.net, one of Egypt's leading job search platforms. The data includes detailed job information across various industries and positions in Egypt.\par
\cf1\fs28 Dataset Features:\cf0\fs22\par
\cf2\fs24 Job Titles: \cf4 The titles of the job positions listed.\par
\cf2 Company Names: \cf4 The names of the companies offering the jobs.\par
\cf2 Locations: \cf4 The geographical locations of the jobs (Cities in Egypt).\par
\cf2 Job Types: \cf4 The employment type (e.g., Full-time, Part-time, Contract).\par
\cf2 Job Category: \cf4 Detailed job descriptions, providing insight into the required skills and responsibilities.\par
\cf0\fs22\par
\cf1\fs28 UI Design:\par
\cf4\fs24 Search input for job title\par
Search button\par
Results table showing companies and salaries\par
Dark theme design with purple color palette\par

